Description: Airslide Systems Inc. is a world leader in 3G-IP convergence solutions for cellular networks.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Airslide Systems Inc. is a provider of 3G-IP convergence solutions for cellular networks. Airslide is a networking company with research, development, and design facilities in Israel. Airslide is the developer of Nebula Gateway technology. Airslide's markets itself as a provider of a cost effective 3G/IP solution for new cellular networks, by providing complimentary solutions for the current backbone infrastructure utilizing cutting edge IP convergence technology. The company’s solutions deal with the setback of dependency on wire-line technology. Airslide's Nebula Family of Gateways provides an IP-based converged cellular network. The company combines, signaling, voice, and data technology and converges them into one efficient cost-effective IP network. This convergence can be deployed through a phased migration, beginning with the SS7 signaling network. Airslide's SMS/IP offloading solution utilizes the SS7 signaling network from the SMS traffic onto an IP network. Following the installation and implementation of the Nebula Gateway SMS/IP solution, this signaling traffic can be offloaded onto an IP network. The company is based New York City, and has an additional office in Herzelia Pituach, Israel.

Description: InterviewTrail.com generates hospital rankings based on aggregate data submitted by residency applicants.
Full Description: InterviewTrail.com generates hospital rankings based on aggregate data submitted by residency applicants.  Each year over 40,000 medical students apply for U.S. residency positions. They submit their hospital rankings to a centralized service, with the hopes of matching at their number one program. But the rankings are put into a lockbox. No one knows how the hospitals are actually ranked. Until now, the U.S. News and World Report has been the only source for hospital rankings.  But by aggregating hospital rankings among our members, we make the hospital rankings game completely objective.  Not only do we provide patients, medical students and doctors with a true aggregation of the best hospitals, but delving a little deeper into the data enables us to tell individual medical students their chances of getting a job at their top hospital -AND- show hospital administrators which other hospitals are competing with them for applicants. In addition, InterviewTrail.com acts as a TripIt for the 40,000 residency applicants who travel the nation each year.  InterviewTrail.com saves money for applicants through a travel affiliation with Expedia. At its core, InterviewTrail.com is a source for hospital rankings based on legitimate, objective ranking data. Through the mass collaboration of over 40,000 of the world's newest doctors each year, InterviewTrail.com aims to redefine the "Best Hospitals" in the U.S.

Our interactive computer-based software helps to facilitate the legal processes for our clients and enable us to prepare complex immigration cases regardless of where our clients reside.  We cater to both corporate and individual clients living throughout the US and internationally. Our office is culturally diverse, with half our staff being first generation immigrants with roots from all over the globe. Our mission is to provide personalized attention that you are unlikely to receive from other larger firms.  You can always count on responsive service and regular updates on your case. We serve clients from many different sectors including healthcare, education and technology.  We deliver first-class client satisfaction to all our clients whether they are a hospital, university, mid-size company, not for profit, or a start-up. In addition, we also have extensive experience in reuniting families and married/engaged couples.  We understand and appreciate that your quality of life, in many cases, is dependent on your eventual visa approval, which we work hard to obtain. We exclusively practice business and family immigration law.  We help employers obtain foreign employees and individualsachieve the American Dream. We are confident in our depth of knowledge, attention to detail and responsiveness in solving the most challenging immigration issues. What We Do:     Exclusively practice business and family immigration law.     We offer a proprietary and state-of-the-art case management program to our clients that allows easy access to their own case status on our secure website.     Our specially created software allows for clients to upload their supporting documents directly.     Offer quick turnaround time (most petitions are prepared with seven (7) working days).     Much of our business come from referrals from former or existing satisfied clients.     We offer direct communication with an attorney or our knowledgeable staff.     Our staff is experienced in preparing all immigrant and non-immigrant petitions and USDOL (PERM) labor certifications.
